                                            <h1 style="color: #ffffff; padding-top: 10px">Career Outlook </h1>
                                            <p style="color: #ffffff; padding-top: 10px; ">Singapore’s strong educational foundation has produced a highly skilled workforce, making it an attractive hub for multinational companies like Unilever, IBM, and General Motors. 
                                                Data scientists, IT professionals, HR specialists, and marketing experts are in high demand.
                                            </p>
                                                <h1 style="color: #ffffff; padding-top: 10px">Working in Singapore as a Student </h1>
                                                <p style="color: #ffffff; padding-top: 10px; ">Indian students with a valid Student Pass issued by the Immigration Checkpoint Authority (ICA) can work part-time for up to 16 hours per week during terms and full-time during vacations, provided their university is approved by the Ministry of Manpower (MOM). 
                                                    Students can work under the following permits:
                                                </p>
                                                
                                            <div style=" padding-top: 10px; padding-left: 20px;"> 
                                                <ul >
                                                <li>Training Work Permit: For students undergoing practical training, valid for six months.</li>
                                                <li>Training Employment Pass: For students in professional training with a monthly income of SGD 3,000, valid for six months.</li>
                                                <li>Work Holiday Pass: For graduates aged 18-25, valid for six months, allowing them to work and holiday in Singapore.</li>
                                                </ul>
                        
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>

