                                            <h1 style="color: #ffffff; padding-top: 10px">Cost of Studying and Living in Singapore</h1>
                                            <p style="color: #ffffff; padding-top: 10px; ">Studying in Singapore can be more affordable than in countries like the UK, USA, or Australia. 
                                                Tuition fees vary depending on whether a student attends a public or private institution.
                                                 Public universities generally offer more economical options.
                                            </p>
                                            <h3  style="color: #ffffff;  ;"> Approximate Annual Fees for Indian Students:</h3>
                                            <div style=" padding-top: 10px; padding-left: 20px;"> 
                                                <ul >
                                                    <li> Pre-University: SGD 21,000 (INR 11,65,000)</li>
                                                    <li> Polytechnic: SGD 10,400 (INR 5,77,000)</li>
                                                    <li> Public University: SGD 17,500 - 24,500 (INR 9,71,000 - 13,59,000)</li>

                                                </ul>
                                            </div> 
                                            <p style="color: #ffffff; padding-top: 10px; ; "> <b>Note:</b> <i> Prices and exchange rates may fluctuate.</i></p>
                                            <h3  style="color: #ffffff;  ;"> Living Costs:</h3>
                                            <p style="color: #ffffff; padding-top: 10px; ; "> <b>Accommodation options include</b></p>
                                            <div style=" padding-top: 10px; padding-left: 20px;"> 
                                                <ul >
                                                    <li> University hostels - $200 – $700 (Approx INR 11,200  INR 39,050)</li>
                                                    <li> Rental apartments- $800 – $2,000 (Approx INR 44,600 – INR 1,11,500)</li>
                                                    <li> Off-campus hostels- $400 (Approx INR 22,300)</li>
                                                    <li> Homestays- $900 – $2000 (Approx INR 50,200 – INR 1,11,500)</li>
                                                    <li> Monthly transportation costs range from SGD 100 to 250.</li>
